Turn the beat structure into the passages the player will read. The engine has
already grouped beats into passages and wired every choice's destination, gate, and
consequence — you contribute only the words: a summary per passage, a label per
choice, a title per ending.

VISION: {{ vision.genre }}, {{ vision.tone }}. Themes: {{ vision.themes | join("; ") }}.

PASSAGE GROUPS (fixed; one passage each):
{% for grp in groups %}
- group {{ grp.index }}{% if grp.is_ending %} [ENDING]{% endif %}{% if grp.gate %} [gated: {{ grp.gate | join(", ") }}]{% endif %}{% if grp.variant_flags %} [VARIANTS needed, one per flag: {{ grp.variant_flags | join(", ") }}]{% endif %}:
{% for b in grp.beats %}
  - {{ b.id }}: {{ b.summary }}
{% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

CHOICES (fixed endpoints; write the label the player clicks):
{% for e in edges %}
- group {{ e.src }} -> group {{ e.dst }}{% if e.requires %} (only shown with {{ e.requires | join(", ") }}){% endif %}{% if e.grants %} (locks in {{ e.grants | join(", ") }}){% endif %}
{% endfor %}

REQUIREMENTS:
- passages: one entry per group: {"group": N, "id": "passage:p-slug", "summary":
  1-2 sentences distilling the group's beats, "ending_title": "..."} — ending_title
  only for [ENDING] groups: short and evocative, no spoilers.
- Groups marked [VARIANTS needed]: same entry but with "variants":
  [{"flag", "id", "summary"}] — one per listed flag, same story moment, genuinely
  different situation per flag. Give the group entry an id and summary anyway (they
  are ignored).
- labels: one entry per choice: {"from": N, "to": N, "label": "..."}. Labels are
  the player's voice: concrete actions, present tense, no outcomes revealed, no
  meta-language ("continue", "go to next scene" are failures — even a single
  onward choice deserves a diegetic line). Labels from the same group must differ.
- Match the tone. Never mention flags, dilemmas, or structure in any player-facing
  text.
